reviews_data.review_text: Such a great used book store. The staff are so warm and welcoming. They have a section just for LGBT books!

reviews_data.review_text: This book shop is so cute and staff is so lovely! I bought a book that I had read before for my cousin and she offered to put it in a gift bag for free (see picture)! They were also giving a tote bag for the first 100 customers (see picture again)! There's a small book nook with a bean bag for your little one. They also sell pretty kindle covers, so even if you're an ebook reader you can stop by. You can also bring an empty bottle to buy shampoo, detergent, etc. by the ounce. The ping pong in front of it is also so fun. You can get a ball from a dispenser for 25 cents, if you have a coin. Someone left a ball by the table for us so we played with that. The whole area is so entertaining. There's also a cookie stall and Hex coffee shop nearby.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for coming to see us and for visiting some of our incredible neighbors, Jiu! We hope we see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Alyssa is the sweetest!  The bookstore has a variety of new and used books along with bookish apparel for all of the bookworms in your life. Pay them a visit and it will not disappoint, it's everything you want from an Indie bookstore!

reviews_data.review_text:
I stumbled upon this bookstore after posting on Facebook about some books I was looking to offload from my (overwhelming) collection, and was happily notified that they are a new/used bookstore. Interactions with both staff members (via FB & in person) were both warm, welcoming and super nice! When we came in today, I loved the cute and accepting atmosphere of this woman-owned small business. You’ve definitely secured a repeat customer here with just one visit!

I also love the selection of Charlotte based authors, as well as their fun selection of bookish/local goodies. Definitely worth a peek if you’re at Camp North End!

reviews_data.review_text: That's Novel Books is located in Camp North End, just outside of downtown Charlotte! They had a great selection and you can't beat their prices! If you're a book lover and live in the Charlotte area, it's a must check out stop!

reviews_data.review_text:
that's novel has quickly become one of my favorite bookstores and communities! they have a great selection of new and used books (plus a great variety of local authors' works too!!), as well as bookish merch from local artists.

i also regularly attend the writing club held here and it's been such a great place for creativity and community. plus, camp northend is SO cute!

5 stars, 10/10, get yoself to that's novel asap!!

reviews_data.review_text: My husband and I just shopped here and LOVED the vibe, the books, and everything. Wonderful selection of books plus a lovely selection of books by Black authors. Love to see it! When we’re passing through Charlotte, we’ll definitely be back here.

reviews_data.review_text: TNB is an awesome local book store situated on a really fun property to explore, Camp North End. It has a regularly updated and expanding offering of books. They also hosts great silent book clubs and other events.

reviews_data.review_text: Eclectic area.  Variety of used books and other items.

reviews_data.review_text: Best little bookstore I've ever been to from all the places I've ever traveled.  I found it via a Google search for used book stores. I truly enjoyed my experience.  I learned they just opened a few days ago as well, and the sign just went up today.  I hope they do wonderful!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Amanda, thank you so much for stopping by and leaving such kind words for our shop! We are so grateful and hope that if you're ever visiting friends in Charlotte again, you stop by to see us as we continue to grow! It was a pleasure to meet you!

reviews_data.review_text: The cutest freaking used bookstore (plus way more) in Charlotte. Located in Camp North End, they have expanded from carrying just used books to multiple local/small business vendors. Always worth stopping in since their book choices are always changing! If you have not been here yet, add it to your list!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your kind words, Chelsea! We so appreciate your support. It means the world to us!

reviews_data.review_text: The cutest bookstore with tons to offer! Such a staple spot in CLT for me.

reviews_data.review_text: More used books than new which I personally love, however it's not a huge or curated book selection. Certainly a fun shop for artisan products like jewelry, t-shirts, soaps, and more! Their painted has selection is beautiful and I can't wait to go back to get one!

reviews_data.review_text: My favorite book store in Charlotte!!! That’s Novel Books is a beautiful curation of used books. I love getting book recommendations from owner, Alyssa. reviews_data.owner_answer: Jane, you're a gem! Thank you for your kind words!

reviews_data.review_text: That's Novel Books is a great addition to the Charlotte area. I've found a lot of great books. The owner is incredibly helpful. She really cares about her customers enjoying their reading experience and it shows in the extra mile she goes for everyone.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much, Jennifer! I love helping you find new books to love. You are a gem!

reviews_data.review_text: Just a tiny assortment of books located inside another store.

reviews_data.review_text: One of the best book stores in Charlotte! Alyssa is the best and will help you find the perfect book!  Love this place!!

reviews_data.review_text: This is our favorite local used book store. The owner is super responsive and will always hold books for you. Also, my daughter absolutely loves their story time with local authors!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Megan! Seeing you and your daughter is always a joy. We so appreciate your support!

reviews_data.review_text: Wonderful used bookstore with a great selection of books and book accessories. The owner Alyssa is very helpful and her passion for books is unlike any others

reviews_data.review_text: If you're not familiar with the independent book seller scene here in Charlotte this one of the places you should get to know. The owner has done a good job curating what's on the shelves. This is a great place to find something you might not otherwise decide to pick up if you were just looking on the 'zon. Periodically the owner also offers "blind date" book selections to help folks fall in love with new genres and writers they might not otherwise be familiar with.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Daniel! We love our Blind Date section. It's a great way to pick up a book you might otherwise overlook!

reviews_data.review_text: Fantastic small business that adds so much to the Charlotte book scene. Very happy they are still open, and not at all hard to find in the heart of Camp North End. They have “Blind Date” books, and a silent reading book club. Go here and take a trip through the shelves. Alyssa is awesome and will help you find whatever book you want.
reviews_data.owner_answer: You are so kind, Mike! We love when you come in and check everything out after your many runs through Charlotte! You're the best.

reviews_data.review_text: Alyssa is the best!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much, Brittney! We love working with you when we get the chance!

reviews_data.review_text: This is a really fun bookstore. The selection isn't vast but still worth a visit.

Love this place! Alyssa is super nice and will hold books for you. I love the Blind Date with a Book she offers! I've purchased a couple of these and have been pleasantly happy! Definitely recommend going here for a great selection of books, at prices that will save you money!

Great used bookstore! Always stocked well and clean. Super adorable atmosphere with chairs to sit and read or get some work done. Outside there's shared seating (picnictables & rockers), too! 💛 10/10 would recommend.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your review! We hope you come see us again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Great Idea!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your review!

reviews_data.review_text: Stumbled upon this book store and I thank The Lord for leading me here. Wonderful collection of books. I especially favored the banned book collection. I’ll definitely be back to add to my collection. We were greeted upon entering the store the young lady was extremely knowledgeable and friendly.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for stopping by and leaving us these kind words, Alesia! We can't wait to see you again!

reviews_data.review_text: Very cute. Good selection. Unique trinkets.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your kind review, Amanda! We hope you come back to see us soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Wonderful selection of used and new books! I never leave here empty handed. They also offer goodies from local small businesses!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Andrea, it's always a joy to see you and your beautiful family stop by our shop! Thank you so much for the kind words!

reviews_data.review_text: That's Novel Books is located in Camp North End, just outside of downtown Charlotte! They had a great selection and you can't beat their prices! If you're a book lover and live in the Charlotte area, it's a must check out stop!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your kind review and for stopping to visit us, Kyra!

reviews_data.review_text:
that's novel has quickly become one of my favorite bookstores and communities! they have a great selection of new and used books (plus a great variety of local authors' works too!!), as well as bookish merch from local artists.

i also regularly attend the writing club held here and it's been such a great place for creativity and community. plus, camp northend is SO cute!

5 stars, 10/10, get yoself to that's novel asap!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Anne, THANK YOU!! Gosh this is such a kind review and we are so, so grateful for you and your support. See you at the next writing club!!

reviews_data.review_text: My husband and I just shopped here and LOVED the vibe, the books, and everything. Wonderful selection of books plus a lovely selection of books by Black authors. Love to see it! When we’re passing through Charlotte, we’ll definitely be back here.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for stopping in, Kenya! We hope you pass through again!

reviews_data.review_text: TNB is an awesome local book store situated on a really fun property to explore, Camp North End. It has a regularly updated and expanding offering of books. They also hosts great silent book clubs and other events.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your kind review, Garrett! Avid readers like you are what keep us going!

reviews_data.review_text: Eclectic area.  Variety of used books and other items.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your review, Theresa! We hope you come back to see us again soon :)

reviews_data.review_text: Sooo cute! And so much fun to wander around and get lost in the aisles! They also host really fun events!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your kind review, Rachel! It means so much! Hope to see you again soon :)

reviews_data.review_text: Best little bookstore I've ever been to from all the places I've ever traveled.  I found it via a Google search for used book stores.  The store is open, airy, light and warm.  The staff was very friendly, and it was good to chat with them.  Fantastic selection of books and gifts, including handmade rings by a local artist.  I truly enjoyed my experience.  I learned they just opened a few days ago as well, and the sign just went up today.  I hope they do wonderful!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Amanda, thank you so much for stopping by and leaving such kind words for our shop! We are so grateful and hope that if you're ever visiting friends in Charlotte again, you stop by to see us as we continue to grow! It was a pleasure to meet you!

reviews_data.review_text: The cutest freaking used bookstore (plus way more) in Charlotte. Located in Camp North End, they have expanded from carrying just used books to multiple local/small business vendors. Always worth stopping in since their book choices are always changing! If you have not been here yet, add it to your list!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your kind words, Chelsea! We so appreciate your support. It means the world to us!

reviews_data.review_text: The cutest bookstore with tons to offer! I chose a “blind date with a book” to take home and it was such a wonderful read- one of those I’ve kept on my shelf as a permanent staple in my home library. The staff is incredible and so welcoming! I frequently revisit to get some of my favorite locally made goodies and never leave without at least one book, even when my TBR is a mile long! Such a staple spot in CLT for me.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Jo, your words have made our day! Thank you so much for your continued support - there are not words to adequately express how much it means to us as a small, independent bookstore.

reviews_data.review_text: A wonderful little bookstore with a great selection of used books! The owner is also fantastic, kind and very helpful in sourcing quality books. A great small business to support and will be going back again!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Maddy you are so sweet! Thank you for your kind words and your ongoing support. We are so grateful for you!

reviews_data.review_text: Great people and shopping experience. Unique finds every time!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your kind review, Tony!

reviews_data.review_text: my favorite local bookstore. the owner is super nice & helpful. small but mighty selection of books across many genres 📚✨
reviews_data.owner_answer: Ben, thank you so much for your kind review! Your words mean so much to us, and we are so grateful for your endless support 💛

reviews_data.review_text: Wonderful bookstore located in Camp North End. A cozy, immaculate, and warm atmosphere. The shop owner is also super bright and a delight. A Charlotte bookstore definitely worth checking out.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Kristina! This means the world to us!

reviews_data.review_text: The store is really cute and the options I’m the boutique side are fantastic, but the book selection is too small to be worth the trip just for this. (A nice little stop if you’re already at Camp Northend.)
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Tracey! Thanks so much for your review. We are in the process of expanding our section in the store and look forward to having you come back and see us soon!

reviews_data.review_text: More used books than new which I personally love, however it's not a huge or curated book selection. Certainly a fun shop for artisan products like jewelry, t-shirts, soaps, and more! Their painted has selection is beautiful and I can't wait to go back to get one!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for coming by, Alicia! We do have a small but mighty collection we are very proud of. We are always looking to expand our book sections and take donations and even pay for books via appointment on our website!

reviews_data.review_text: My favorite book store in Charlotte!!! That’s Novel Books is a beautiful curation of used books. I love getting book recommendations from owner, Alyssa. If you aren’t local (or even if you are!) her monthly book subscription is amazing! As well as the monthly silent book club they put on. It’s a treat to have this in our city.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Jane, you're a gem! Thank you for your kind words!

reviews_data.review_text: That's Novel Books is a great addition to the Charlotte area. I've found a lot of great books. The owner is incredibly helpful. I told her the type of book I had just finished and loved, she pulled an assortment of similar books. She really cares about her customers enjoying their reading experience and it shows in the extra mile she goes for everyone.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much, Jennifer! I love helping you find new books to love. You are a gem!

reviews_data.review_text: Just a tiny assortment of books located inside another store.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We are tiny, but mighty! Thank you for stopping by :)

reviews_data.review_text: One of the best book stores in Charlotte! Alyssa is the best and will help you find the perfect book!  Love this place!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so, so much for your kind words! We absolutely love helping folks find the book for them.

reviews_data.review_text: This is our favorite local used book store. The owner is super responsive and will always hold books for you. Also, my daughter absolutely loves their story time with local authors!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Megan! Seeing you and your daughter is always a joy. We so appreciate your support!

reviews_data.review_text: Wonderful used bookstore with a great selection of books and book accessories. The owner Alyssa is very helpful and her passion for books is unlike any others
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Ryan! You're so kind!

reviews_data.review_text: If you're not familiar with the independent book seller scene here in Charlotte this one of the places you should get to know. The owner has done a good job curating what's on the shelves. This is a great place to find something you might not otherwise decide to pick up if you were just looking on the 'zon. Periodically the owner also offers "blind date" book selections to help folks fall in love with new genres and writers they might not otherwise be familiar with.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Daniel! We love our Blind Date section. It's a great way to pick up a book you might otherwise overlook!

reviews_data.review_text: Fantastic small business that adds so much to the Charlotte book scene. Very happy they are still open, and not at all hard to find in the heart of Camp North End. They have “Blind Date” books, and a silent reading book club. Go here and take a trip through the shelves. Alyssa is awesome and will help you find whatever book you want.
reviews_data.owner_answer: You are so kind, Mike! We love when you come in and check everything out after your many runs through Charlotte! You're the best.

reviews_data.review_text: Alyssa is the best!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much, Brittney! We love working with you when we get the chance!

reviews_data.review_text: This is a really fun bookstore. The selection isn't vast but still worth a visit.

Love this place! Alyssa is super nice and will hold books for you. I love the Blind Date with a Book she offers! I've purchased a couple of these and have been pleasantly happy! Definitely recommend going here for a great selection of books, at prices that will save you money!

Great used bookstore! Always stocked well and clean. Super adorable atmosphere with chairs to sit and read or get some work done. Outside there's shared seating (picnictables & rockers), too! 💛 10/10 would recommend.
